description.text:
A parametric ruler which can be used in other designs as a rough guide to sizes. Just use the &quot;use &lt;ruler_100mm.scad&quot; instruction at the top of your project and then call it by using &quot;ruler_mm();&quot;  
This is provided on a &quot;do anything you like with it&quot; basis except trying to patent it or otherwise restrict its use or prevent it from being freely available....  
I wouldn't try to print this! It almost certainly wouldn't work very well. The idea is just to use it to guide your OpenSCAD designs.

Print two copies then glue them together and hand them out in shame because you forgot to buy Xmas presents for everyone on your list.
If you want to print it thinner then download &quot;good_for_1_print_coin 2 Larger Thinner.stl&quot;
The thinner prints almost as nice but a little thinner.  Less plastic but more joy when you hand it out because you completely forgot about someone on your Xmas list.
